{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"You know, I'm struck by how one of the implicit themes of TED"},{"time":5000,"text":"is compassion, these very moving demonstrations we've just seen:"},{"time":9000,"text":"HIV in Africa, President Clinton last night."},{"time":13000,"text":"And I'd like to do a little collateral thinking, if you will,"},{"time":18000,"text":"about compassion and bring it from the global level to the personal."},{"time":23000,"text":"I'm a psychologist, but rest assured,"},{"time":25000,"text":"I will not bring it to the scrotal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":32000,"text":"There was a very important study done a while ago"},{"time":34000,"text":"at Princeton Theological Seminary that speaks to why it is"},{"time":39000,"text":"that when all of us have so many opportunities to help,"},{"time":42000,"text":"we do sometimes, and we don't other times."},{"time":46000,"text":"A group of divinity students at the Princeton Theological Seminary"},{"time":50000,"text":"were told that they were going to give a practice sermon"},{"time":54000,"text":"and they were each given a sermon topic."},{"time":57000,"text":"Half of those students were given, as a topic,"},{"time":60000,"text":"the parable of the Good Samaritan:"},{"time":62000,"text":"the man who stopped the stranger in --"},{"time":65000,"text":"to help the stranger in need by the side of the road."},{"time":67000,"text":"Half were given random Bible topics."},{"time":70000,"text":"Then one by one, they were told they had to go to another building"},{"time":74000,"text":"and give their sermon."},{"time":75000,"text":"As they went from the first building to the second,"},{"time":78000,"text":"each of them passed a man who was bent over and moaning,"},{"time":82000,"text":"clearly in need. The question is: Did they stop to help?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":86000,"text":"The more interesting question is:"},{"time":88000,"text":"Did it matter they were contemplating the parable"},{"time":91000,"text":"of the Good Samaritan? Answer: No, not at all."},{"time":96000,"text":"What turned out to determine whether someone would stop"},{"time":99000,"text":"and help a stranger in need"},{"time":100000,"text":"was how much of a hurry they thought they were in --"},{"time":104000,"text":"were they feeling they were late, or were they absorbed"},{"time":108000,"text":"in what they were going to talk about."},{"time":110000,"text":"And this is, I think, the predicament of our lives:"},{"time":113000,"text":"that we don't take every opportunity to help"},{"time":117000,"text":"because our focus is in the wrong direction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":120000,"text":"There's a new field in brain science, social neuroscience."},{"time":124000,"text":"This studies the circuitry in two people's brains"},{"time":128000,"text":"that activates while they interact."},{"time":130000,"text":"And the new thinking about compassion from social neuroscience"},{"time":134000,"text":"is that our default wiring is to help."},{"time":138000,"text":"That is to say, if we attend to the other person,"},{"time":143000,"text":"we automatically empathize, we automatically feel with them."},{"time":147000,"text":"There are these newly identified neurons, mirror neurons,"},{"time":149000,"text":"that act like a neuro Wi-Fi, activating in our brain"},{"time":153000,"text":"exactly the areas activated in theirs. We feel \"with\" automatically."},{"time":157000,"text":"And if that person is in need, if that person is suffering,"},{"time":162000,"text":"we're automatically prepared to help. At least that's the argument."}]},{"cues":[{"time":166000,"text":"But then the question is: Why don't we?"},{"time":169000,"text":"And I think this speaks to a spectrum"},{"time":172000,"text":"that goes from complete self-absorption,"},{"time":175000,"text":"to noticing, to empathy and to compassion."},{"time":177000,"text":"And the simple fact is, if we are focused on ourselves,"},{"time":182000,"text":"if we're preoccupied, as we so often are throughout the day,"},{"time":185000,"text":"we don't really fully notice the other."},{"time":188000,"text":"And this difference between the self and the other focus"},{"time":190000,"text":"can be very subtle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":191000,"text":"I was doing my taxes the other day, and I got to the point"},{"time":195000,"text":"where I was listing all of the donations I gave,"},{"time":198000,"text":"and I had an epiphany, it was -- I came to my check"},{"time":201000,"text":"to the Seva Foundation and I noticed that I thought,"},{"time":204000,"text":"boy, my friend Larry Brilliant would really be happy"},{"time":207000,"text":"that I gave money to Seva."},{"time":208000,"text":"Then I realized that what I was getting from giving"},{"time":211000,"text":"was a narcissistic hit -- that I felt good about myself."},{"time":215000,"text":"Then I started to think about the people in the Himalayas"},{"time":220000,"text":"whose cataracts would be helped, and I realized"},{"time":223000,"text":"that I went from this kind of narcissistic self-focus"},{"time":227000,"text":"to altruistic joy, to feeling good"},{"time":230000,"text":"for the people that were being helped. I think that's a motivator."}]},{"cues":[{"time":234000,"text":"But this distinction between focusing on ourselves"},{"time":237000,"text":"and focusing on others"},{"time":238000,"text":"is one that I encourage us all to pay attention to."},{"time":241000,"text":"You can see it at a gross level in the world of dating."},{"time":245000,"text":"I was at a sushi restaurant a while back"},{"time":248000,"text":"and I overheard two women talking about the brother of one woman,"},{"time":252000,"text":"who was in the singles scene. And this woman says,"},{"time":255000,"text":"\"My brother is having trouble getting dates,"},{"time":257000,"text":"so he's trying speed dating.\" I don't know if you know speed dating?"},{"time":259000,"text":"Women sit at tables and men go from table to table,"},{"time":263000,"text":"and there's a clock and a bell, and at five minutes, bingo,"},{"time":267000,"text":"the conversation ends and the woman can decide"},{"time":269000,"text":"whether to give her card or her email address to the man"},{"time":273000,"text":"for follow up. And this woman says,"},{"time":275000,"text":"\"My brother's never gotten a card, and I know exactly why."},{"time":279000,"text":"The moment he sits down, he starts talking non-stop about himself;"},{"time":284000,"text":"he never asks about the woman.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":286000,"text":"And I was doing some research in the Sunday Styles section"},{"time":291000,"text":"of The New York Times, looking at the back stories of marriages --"},{"time":294000,"text":"because they're very interesting -- and I came to the marriage"},{"time":297000,"text":"of Alice Charney Epstein. And she said"},{"time":300000,"text":"that when she was in the dating scene,"},{"time":303000,"text":"she had a simple test she put people to."},{"time":306000,"text":"The test was: from the moment they got together,"},{"time":308000,"text":"how long it would take the guy to ask her a question"},{"time":311000,"text":"with the word \"you\" in it."},{"time":313000,"text":"And apparently Epstein aced the test, therefore the article."}]},{"cues":[{"time":317000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":318000,"text":"Now this is a -- it's a little test"},{"time":320000,"text":"I encourage you to try out at a party."},{"time":322000,"text":"Here at TED there are great opportunities."},{"time":326000,"text":"The Harvard Business Review recently had an article called"},{"time":329000,"text":"\"The Human Moment,\" about how to make real contact"},{"time":332000,"text":"with a person at work. And they said, well,"},{"time":335000,"text":"the fundamental thing you have to do is turn off your BlackBerry,"},{"time":339000,"text":"close your laptop, end your daydream"},{"time":343000,"text":"and pay full attention to the person."},{"time":346000,"text":"There is a newly coined word in the English language"},{"time":351000,"text":"for the moment when the person we're with whips out their BlackBerry"},{"time":354000,"text":"or answers that cell phone, and all of a sudden we don't exist."},{"time":358000,"text":"The word is \"pizzled\": it's a combination of puzzled and pissed off."}]},{"cues":[{"time":362000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":365000,"text":"I think it's quite apt. It's our empathy, it's our tuning in"},{"time":372000,"text":"which separates us from Machiavellians or sociopaths."},{"time":375000,"text":"I have a brother-in-law who's an expert on horror and terror --"},{"time":380000,"text":"he wrote the Annotated Dracula, the Essential Frankenstein --"},{"time":383000,"text":"he was trained as a Chaucer scholar,"},{"time":384000,"text":"but he was born in Transylvania"},{"time":386000,"text":"and I think it affected him a little bit."},{"time":388000,"text":"At any rate, at one point my brother-in-law, Leonard,"},{"time":392000,"text":"decided to write a book about a serial killer."},{"time":394000,"text":"This is a man who terrorized the very vicinity we're in"},{"time":398000,"text":"many years ago. He was known as the Santa Cruz strangler."},{"time":401000,"text":"And before he was arrested, he had murdered his grandparents,"},{"time":405000,"text":"his mother and five co-eds at UC Santa Cruz."}]},{"cues":[{"time":409000,"text":"So my brother-in-law goes to interview this killer"},{"time":412000,"text":"and he realizes when he meets him"},{"time":414000,"text":"that this guy is absolutely terrifying."},{"time":416000,"text":"For one thing, he's almost seven feet tall."},{"time":418000,"text":"But that's not the most terrifying thing about him."},{"time":421000,"text":"The scariest thing is that his IQ is 160: a certified genius."},{"time":427000,"text":"But there is zero correlation between IQ and emotional empathy,"},{"time":431000,"text":"feeling with the other person."},{"time":433000,"text":"They're controlled by different parts of the brain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":436000,"text":"So at one point, my brother-in-law gets up the courage"},{"time":439000,"text":"to ask the one question he really wants to know the answer to,"},{"time":441000,"text":"and that is: how could you have done it?"},{"time":444000,"text":"Didn't you feel any pity for your victims?"},{"time":446000,"text":"These were very intimate murders -- he strangled his victims."},{"time":450000,"text":"And the strangler says very matter-of-factly,"},{"time":452000,"text":"\"Oh no. If I'd felt the distress, I could not have done it."},{"time":457000,"text":"I had to turn that part of me off. I had to turn that part of me off.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":463000,"text":"And I think that that is very troubling,"},{"time":469000,"text":"and in a sense, I've been reflecting on turning that part of us off."},{"time":473000,"text":"When we focus on ourselves in any activity,"},{"time":476000,"text":"we do turn that part of ourselves off if there's another person."},{"time":480000,"text":"Think about going shopping and think about the possibilities"},{"time":485000,"text":"of a compassionate consumerism."},{"time":488000,"text":"Right now, as Bill McDonough has pointed out,"},{"time":492000,"text":"the objects that we buy and use have hidden consequences."},{"time":496000,"text":"We're all unwitting victims of a collective blind spot."},{"time":500000,"text":"We don't notice and don't notice that we don't notice"},{"time":503000,"text":"the toxic molecules emitted by a carpet or by the fabric on the seats."},{"time":510000,"text":"Or we don't know if that fabric is a technological"},{"time":515000,"text":"or manufacturing nutrient; it can be reused"},{"time":519000,"text":"or does it just end up at landfill? In other words,"},{"time":521000,"text":"we're oblivious to the ecological and public health"},{"time":527000,"text":"and social and economic justice consequences"},{"time":530000,"text":"of the things we buy and use."},{"time":534000,"text":"In a sense, the room itself is the elephant in the room,"},{"time":538000,"text":"but we don't see it. And we've become victims"},{"time":542000,"text":"of a system that points us elsewhere. Consider this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":546000,"text":"There's a wonderful book called"},{"time":550000,"text":"Stuff: The Hidden Life of Everyday Objects."},{"time":553000,"text":"And it talks about the back story of something like a t-shirt."},{"time":556000,"text":"And it talks about where the cotton was grown"},{"time":559000,"text":"and the fertilizers that were used and the consequences"},{"time":561000,"text":"for soil of that fertilizer. And it mentions, for instance,"},{"time":565000,"text":"that cotton is very resistant to textile dye;"},{"time":568000,"text":"about 60 percent washes off into wastewater."},{"time":571000,"text":"And it's well known by epidemiologists that kids"},{"time":574000,"text":"who live near textile works tend to have high rates of leukemia."},{"time":580000,"text":"There's a company, Bennett and Company, that supplies Polo.com,"},{"time":585000,"text":"Victoria's Secret -- they, because of their CEO, who's aware of this,"},{"time":591000,"text":"in China formed a joint venture with their dye works"},{"time":595000,"text":"to make sure that the wastewater"},{"time":597000,"text":"would be properly taken care of before it returned to the groundwater."},{"time":601000,"text":"Right now, we don't have the option to choose the virtuous t-shirt"},{"time":606000,"text":"over the non-virtuous one. So what would it take to do that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":613000,"text":"Well, I've been thinking. For one thing,"},{"time":616000,"text":"there's a new electronic tagging technology that allows any store"},{"time":621000,"text":"to know the entire history of any item on the shelves in that store."},{"time":626000,"text":"You can track it back to the factory. Once you can track it"},{"time":628000,"text":"back to the factory, you can look at the manufacturing processes"},{"time":632000,"text":"that were used to make it, and if it's virtuous,"},{"time":636000,"text":"you can label it that way. Or if it's not so virtuous,"},{"time":640000,"text":"you can go into -- today, go into any store,"},{"time":644000,"text":"put your scanner on a palm onto a barcode,"},{"time":647000,"text":"which will take you to a website."},{"time":649000,"text":"They have it for people with allergies to peanuts."},{"time":652000,"text":"That website could tell you things about that object."},{"time":655000,"text":"In other words, at point of purchase,"},{"time":656000,"text":"we might be able to make a compassionate choice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":660000,"text":"There's a saying in the world of information science:"},{"time":666000,"text":"ultimately everybody will know everything."},{"time":669000,"text":"And the question is: will it make a difference?"},{"time":673000,"text":"Some time ago when I was working for The New York Times,"},{"time":677000,"text":"it was in the '80s, I did an article"},{"time":679000,"text":"on what was then a new problem in New York --"},{"time":681000,"text":"it was homeless people on the streets."},{"time":683000,"text":"And I spent a couple of weeks going around with a social work agency"},{"time":687000,"text":"that ministered to the homeless. And I realized seeing the homeless"},{"time":690000,"text":"through their eyes that almost all of them were psychiatric patients"},{"time":695000,"text":"that had nowhere to go. They had a diagnosis. It made me --"},{"time":700000,"text":"what it did was to shake me out of the urban trance where,"},{"time":704000,"text":"when we see, when we're passing someone who's homeless"},{"time":707000,"text":"in the periphery of our vision, it stays on the periphery."},{"time":712000,"text":"We don't notice and therefore we don't act."}]},{"cues":[{"time":717000,"text":"One day soon after that -- it was a Friday -- at the end of the day,"},{"time":722000,"text":"I went down -- I was going down to the subway. It was rush hour"},{"time":725000,"text":"and thousands of people were streaming down the stairs."},{"time":727000,"text":"And all of a sudden as I was going down the stairs"},{"time":729000,"text":"I noticed that there was a man slumped to the side,"},{"time":732000,"text":"shirtless, not moving, and people were just stepping over him --"},{"time":737000,"text":"hundreds and hundreds of people."},{"time":739000,"text":"And because my urban trance had been somehow weakened,"},{"time":743000,"text":"I found myself stopping to find out what was wrong."},{"time":747000,"text":"The moment I stopped, half a dozen other people"},{"time":750000,"text":"immediately ringed the same guy."},{"time":752000,"text":"And we found out that he was Hispanic, he didn't speak any English,"},{"time":754000,"text":"he had no money, he'd been wandering the streets for days, starving,"},{"time":759000,"text":"and he'd fainted from hunger."},{"time":760000,"text":"Immediately someone went to get orange juice,"},{"time":762000,"text":"someone brought a hotdog, someone brought a subway cop."},{"time":765000,"text":"This guy was back on his feet immediately."},{"time":768000,"text":"But all it took was that simple act of noticing,"},{"time":773000,"text":"and so I'm optimistic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":774000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":775000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}